The paper deals with the reachability problem for networks of timed communicating processes, which involves formal verification of systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also uses quantifier elimination and reduction to counter automata with registers, which are techniques commonly used in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the evolution of clocks and timing constraints, which are topics relevant to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with networks of processes communicating with each other, which is a topic relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
